  "text": "The sensitivity of the EIT systems ranges from approximately 77% to 90%. It was found to have a limited accuracy at higher frequencies. At higher frequencies (more than 100 kHz), the measurement hardware introduces an additional capacitive artifact, possibly caused by the distant location of the current source circuit with respect to the array of electrodes, which alters the impedance measurements. This limits the operating frequency to a maximum frequency of 100 kHz in order to produce decent images [CITATION_1] .",
